'''Satō Jōjitsu''' (佐藤 誠実, also read as Satō Nobuzane; December 28, 1839 – March 31, 1908) was a Japanese scholar of [[Kokugaku]] (national studies) from the late [[Edo period]] to the [[Meiji period]].

== Biography ==
Satō was born at {{ill|Shogyōji Temple (Taitō Ward)|ja|正行寺 (台東区)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a Jōdo Shinshū temple in {{ill|Asakusa|ja|浅草|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Edo]] (present-day {{ill|Taitō Ward|ja|台東区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Tokyo]]). His childhood name was Zōshu, and his pseudonym was Mokuzai.

From a young age, he served as the head priest of his family temple. He later studied Chinese classics under {{ill|Azumi Gonsai|ja|安積艮斎|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and Kokugaku under {{ill|Kurokawa Harumura|ja|黒川春村|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

After the [[Meiji Restoration]], in 1872, he joined the [[Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology|Ministry of Education]] (then known as the Ministry of Education). Later, he worked at the {{ill|Genrōin|ja|元老院 (日本)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a precursor to the [[Imperial Diet (Japan)|Imperial Diet]]. 

In 1880, he contributed to the compilation of the ''{{ill|Kojiruien|ja|古事類苑|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'', a comprehensive encyclopedic work, alongside {{ill|Hiroike Chikurō|ja|廣池千九郎|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. When the project was transferred to the [[Jingū Administration Office]] in 1895, he was appointed as the chief editor.

In recognition of his contributions, he was awarded the title of [[Doctor of Letters (Japan)|Doctor of Letters]] in 1899.

== Academic Career ==
In 1883, he became a lecturer in the classics department at [[Tokyo University]] (later {{ill|Tokyo Imperial University|ja|東京帝国大学|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), and in 1891, he was appointed a professor of classical studies at the {{ill|Tokyo Music School (former)|ja|東京音楽学校 (旧制)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Major Works ==
=== Books ===
* ''Nihon Kyōikushi'' (日本教育史, ''History of Japanese Education'') – A textbook for normal schools (師範学校):
** {{Cite book|title=日本教育史 修訂 巻上 (Nihon Kyōikushi Shūtei, Vol. 1)|year=1943|publisher=十一組出版部|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/1461357}}
** {{Cite book|title=日本教育史 修訂 巻下 (Nihon Kyōikushi Shūtei, Vol. 2)|year=1943|publisher=十一組出版部|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/1461357/1/156}}
* ''Satō Seijitsu Hakushi Ritsuryō Kakushiki Ronshū'' (佐藤誠実博士律令格式論集) – Collection of his research on the Ritsuryō system (1991, {{ill|Kujaku Shoin|ja|汲古書院|qq=draft|qq=draft}})
* ''Gogaku Shinan'' (語学指南, ''Guide to Language Studies'', 1879):
** {{Cite book|title=語学指南 巻1|year=1879|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/992000}}
** {{Cite book|title=語学指南 巻2|year=1879|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/992001}}
** {{Cite book|title=語学指南 巻3|year=1879|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/992002}}
** {{Cite book|title=語学指南 巻4|year=1879|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/992003}}

=== Selected Papers ===
* ''訓点之誤'' (Errors in Kunten Annotations), in ''{{ill|Ōyashimagakai Journal|ja|大八州学会雑誌|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'' (1891)
* ''五十音考'' (A Study of the Japanese Syllabary), in ''{{ill|Tōkyō Meikeikai Journal|ja|東京茗渓会雑誌|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'' (1891)
* ''続日本紀を上る表の約解'' (Annotated Table of the Shoku Nihongi), serialized in ''{{ill|Kokugakuin Journal|ja|國學院雜誌|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'' (1899)
* ''律令考'' (A Study of the Ritsuryō System), serialized in ''{{ill|Kokugakuin Journal|ja|國學院雜誌|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'' (1899–1900)

